# here we use your search algorithm to find a trajectory

from commonroad.prediction.prediction import TrajectoryPrediction
from commonroad_cc.collision_detection.pycrcc_collision_dispatch import create_collision_object
from commonroad_cc.visualization.draw_dispatch import draw_object as draw_it
from IPython.display import clear_output



def search(path, status, maxTreeDepth):
    # update the status dict for visualization in your search algorithm
    res = MP.search_alg(mp.Successors, maxTreeDepth, status) # calls your search function
    if res is None:
        return
    clear_output(wait=True)
    path.value = res[0]
    if len(res[1]) > 0:
        print("Found primitives")
    for primitive in res[1]:
        print(primitive)

manager = Manager()
    
path = manager.Value('path', None)
status = manager.Value('status', None)

# initialize status
stat = {}
stat['cost_so_far'] = 0
stat['currentPath'] = []
status.value = stat

maxTreeDepth = 100 # maximum number of concatenated primitives

# start search process
searchProcess = Process(target=search, args=(path, status, maxTreeDepth))
searchProcess.start()


fig = plt.figure(figsize=(11,13))

def draw_figure():
    plt.clf()
    draw_object(scenario)
    draw_object(list(planning_task.planning_problem_dict.values())[planningProblem_idx])
    plt.gca().set_aspect('equal')
    plt.gca().set_axis_off()
    plt.margins(0,0)
    plt.show()
    
draw_figure()

while True:
    time.sleep(1)
    if not searchProcess.is_alive():
        break
    
    statusStr = "cost_so_far:", status.value['cost_so_far']
    statusStr += "timeStep:", status.value['currentPath'][-1].time_step
    statusStr += "orientation:",status.value['currentPath'][-1].orientation
    statusStr += "velocity:", status.value['currentPath'][-1].velocity
    print (statusStr, end="\r")
    
    # visualize current path
    if len(status.value['currentPath']) > 0:
        draw_figure()
        trajPath = Trajectory(0, status.value['currentPath'][0:])
        traj_pred = TrajectoryPrediction(trajectory=trajPath, shape=egoShape)
        co = create_collision_object(traj_pred)
        draw_it(co, draw_params={'collision': {'facecolor': 'magenta'}})
    
    fig.canvas.draw()    

searchProcess.join()

status = status.value
path = path.value

# visualize trajectory
if len(status['currentPath']) > 0:
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(11,13))
    draw_figure()
    trajPath = Trajectory(0, status['currentPath'][0:])
    traj_pred = TrajectoryPrediction(trajectory=trajPath, shape=egoShape)
    co = create_collision_object(traj_pred)
    draw_it(co, draw_params={'collision': {'facecolor': 'magenta'}})
    fig.canvas.draw()  
    
print("Done")
if len(path) > 1:
    print("Found path")
else:
    print("No path")

if len(path) > 1:
    print ("Found solution")

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))

def get_state_at_time(t):
    for i in range(0, len(path)):
        state = path[i]
        if (state.time_step >= t):
            return state
    return path[-1]
    
def draw(t):
    print("current time stamp: ", t)
    plt.clf()
    #axes = plt.gca()
    #axes.set_xlim([-20,100])
    #axes.set_ylim([-20,100])
    draw_object(scenario.lanelet_network)
    draw_object(scenario.occupancies_at_time_step(t))
    draw_object(list(planning_task.planning_problem_dict.values())[planningProblem_idx])

    if path is not None:
        state = get_state_at_time(t)
        stateTraj = Trajectory(int(state.time_step), [state])
        traj_pred = TrajectoryPrediction(trajectory=stateTraj, shape=egoShape)
        co = create_collision_object(traj_pred)
        draw_it(co)

# use the slider to have at look at every time stamp of your planned trajectory
widgets.interact(draw, t=widgets.IntSlider(min=0,max=path[-1].time_step,step=1,value=0))

from commonroad.common.solution_writer import CommonRoadSolutionWriter, VehicleModel, VehicleType, CostFunction
from commonroad.scenario.trajectory import Trajectory, State

# prepare trajectory
ks_state_list = list()
for pathElem in path:
    ks_state_list.append(State(**{'position': pathElem.position, 'velocity': pathElem.velocity, 'steering_angle': 0, 'orientation': pathElem.orientation, 'time_step': pathElem.time_step}))
trajectory_ks = Trajectory(path[0].time_step, ks_state_list)

# write solution to a xml file
csw = CommonRoadSolutionWriter(output_dir=os.getcwd(), scenario_id=scenario_id, step_size=0.1,
                               vehicle_type=VehicleType.VW_VANAGON, vehicle_model=VehicleModel.KS,
                               cost_function=CostFunction.SA1)

# add trajectory solution
csw.add_solution_trajectory(trajectory_ks, list(planning_task.planning_problem_dict.values())[planningProblem_idx].planning_problem_id)

csw.write_to_file(overwrite=True)
